 in routinisierte Praktiken 'eingeschrieben', doch aufgrund der praktischen und ethischen Komplexität des Alltags liegt ein 'richtiger' Konsum keineswegs auf der Hand.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aConsumers' behaviorvMoral and ethical aspects. 0aConsumption (Economics)vMoral and ethical aspects. 0aMarketingvMoral and ethical aspects. 4aDistinktion. 4aEssen. 4aEsskultur. 4aEthik. 4aKonsum. 4aKultur. 4aKultursoziologie. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aSoziologie. 4aWirtschaft. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aConsumption.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aEconomy.  aFood Studies.  aSociology of Culture.  aSociology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2010-2013z9783110352856oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Sozialw. 2010-2013z9783110370713oZDB-23-TSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2013z9783110401219oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839424520zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839424520423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839424520/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TGPb2013  aZDB-23-TSOc2010d2013  aZDB-23-TSWc2010d2013